    LETS GET STRAIGHT DOWN TO BUSINESS

    ​

    In this bite you will learn how to build a solid foundation to ensure you hit the ground running. Trying to acquire a business without taking this step is like building your house with a straw roof.

    ​

    Business is war, you have to think strategically and in structured steps in order to command territory. You are playing against knights in armour. You wouldn't go to war naked without armour would you? The same principles apply in this game, prepare a solid foundation to command and conquer.

    ​

    Follow the steps in this program and it will show you exactly how to make your deals happen. 

    ​

    BRAND NAME

    SPV & Brand name Guidance
    Mute
    SPV & Brand name Guidance

    Pick a name for your new brand and SPV company  (they can both be the same name). 

    ​

    You need your company set up and properly positioned so that you can use it as you'r holding company to acquire your new business. This is the most professional way to make an acquisition. 

    ​

    Once you make your first acquisition your SPV will invoice the business that you acquired most likely on a monthly basis for example (management consultancy fee invoice), this is how you will get paid. Your SPV will own the share capital in your newly acquired business. 

    ​

     

    WEBSITE & MISSION STATEMENT

    Positioning your brand

     

    You will need to build and design a website for your new acquisition company so that you are properly positioned to make your first acquisition. The main functions of your company are as follows:-

    ​

    • Acquisition / Holding company (Your company will hold share capital in the new business you acquire)

    • Management/consultancy activities (You company will manage and consult to the new business which you acquire)

    ​

    You can see an example of one of our companies in USA below. This example of a business Ken is in direct partnership with one of his mentees.
